RoutingInfo.AdditionalInformation: The IMSI complies with the GSM 03.03 and ITU-T E.212 and has a fixed length of 15 digits. The MSISDN complies with the GSM 03.03 and ITU-T E.164 has a length of 13 digits. Number portability was introduced on 01st September 2008. This means that TIM Brazil customers can have a MSISDN, which is taken from any Brazil mobile network NDC. In Brazil we have other six mobile companies: Claro, VIVO, OI, CTBC, Sercomtel and Unicel. TIM uses RAN Sharing on LTE in some places sharing E.212 72499.
